The paper deals with algorithms for hypergraphs, which are a fundamental data structure in computer science. The problem of enumerating hitting sets is a classic problem in computational complexity and is closely related to the set cover problem, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science. The paper also discusses the application of the algorithm to data profiling, which is a topic in databases and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
